import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the cx field?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_5_names = data['name'].value_counts().nlargest(5)
    sns.barplot(x=top_5_names.index, y=top_5_names.values)
    plt.title('What are the top 5 names in the name field?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = ((data['cx']**2) + (data['cy']**2))**0.5
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', label=f'mean: {data["distance"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the distance between cx and cy fields?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
